                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 97rb: Parchment made of a goat slaughtered while a dead body leaves (the house).  </q>
                           Written in Tǝgrǝňňa by the scribe Wäldä Muse; it concerns an unidentified practice of distinguishing a folio made of a goat which was slaughtered when a body of the dead person left for the church (?).
